F  I  L  M  festivals remind me of film class, college. Filmmakers and movie lovers, artists, students, creators coalesce in the tiniest of spaces or grand ballrooms and theaters all over the world to see short and feature length narrative films, and documentaries. I can never get enough. Behind the camera or on film, I love being part of the story. A story, that hopefully can change one mind, one heart, or even the world. And so I keep going. My cinematic vision, or favorite movies may be different than yours, but no matter where we are on this journey, above the line, or just starting out, if your passion and focus is anything like mine, then it’s only a matter of when, not if. 

#tbt to the US Premier of Angels in Rocket Field, honored with several nominations at The International Christian Film Festival. @icffofficial @angelsinrocketfield @sagaftra @gafilmoffice @thehawkswoopsproductions

F  R  O  M  the archives. 
Not long after this headshot was taken, I received my SAG card. Over the last 25 years (not including a decade-long break from acting) @sagaftra protected me, saw that I was paid fairly and I’ve been a proud member since that day. Like many business models change, this industry has also. A unique business with many moving parts, it has seen advancements and changes very quickly. The actors, writers, and crew, need to be paid and protected congruent to these changes.  I stand firm with my fellow union members as we coalesce to fight and have our voice heard over fair pay, protection and benefits that any “employee” would fight for, and in which we work hard for. Without the writers who create the characters, and without the actors who bring them to life, we would not see the sublime art that we binge watch, that inspires us and has entertained us, impacted lives, created trends, memes, set examples to follow, created legends, scenes and moments on film that are unforgettable. 
This is huge. Historical. I’m hoping and praying we can all reach a fair agreement, and that is to simply consider writers and actors, pay us and protect us so we can all move forward enthusiastically, bolstered by the recognition and acknowledgment we deserve, so we can go back to doing what we love!

S O  many tremendous takeaways learned this year, on set, in classes and workshops, from fellow creatives, artists, casting directors, my coaches, my agent, my Atlanta SAG-AFTRA family, thank you is not enough! I’m grateful for these auditions I’ve been having as I wrap up 2023, and all of the auditions and callbacks, avail checks, I had this year, one step closer. I have so much fun bringing my version to each role! As Gil Junger, drilled into my head, “don’t think just be”, not overthinking my auditions, has been career changing! Thankful and humbled for the strike being over, what we gained, what we learned, and how we came together in solidarity is something I hold close to my heart. 
Very excited for what’s next, ready for lighting to strike! 
So much gratitude! So much to celebrate! The best is yet to come 💯✨
